            ContentJson = """{"title":"Financial Reports Field Reference","groups":[{"heading":"When These Reports Apply","items":[{"label":"Forge keeps the books","value":"The built-in Financial Reports run only when Forge keeps your own books. They are meaningful only when no outside accounting provider (QuickBooks, Xero, etc.) is connected."},{"label":"One or the other","value":"You either run Forge's books or hand bookkeeping to an outside provider, never both. Connecting a provider hands the books to it, so these reports go quiet."},{"label":"Availability","value":"The whole Accounting area stays hidden until the built-in books are switched on for your install."},{"label":"Read-only","value":"Every report reads your posted activity. You view what has already posted; you don't edit transactions on these pages. Period Close and Bank Reconciliation are the only pages with actions."},{"label":"Status label","value":"Most reports carry a header label answering 'does this tie out?' Green (Balanced, Reconciled, Ties to control) means it agrees with its control total. Red or amber (Out of Balance, Variance, Difference) means take a look before relying on the numbers."}]},{"heading":"AP Aging","items":[{"label":"Purpose","value":"What you owe vendors, sorted by how long each bill has been outstanding."},{"label":"Rows","value":"One row per vendor, with an amount in each age bucket plus an Open balance. The first column stays put as you scroll sideways."},{"label":"Age buckets","value":"The standard buckets are 0-30, 31-60, 61-90, and 91+ days (up to six can appear). Each column sorts and shows currency, right-aligned."},{"label":"Totals row","value":"The bottom row sums each bucket and shows the grand Open total."},{"label":"Status label","value":"'Ties to control' (green) when the report agrees with your accounts-payable control account, or 'Out of Balance' (red)."}]},{"heading":"AR Aging","items":[{"label":"Purpose","value":"Who owes you money, sorted by how long each invoice has been outstanding."},{"label":"Rows","value":"One row per customer, with an amount in each age bucket plus an Open balance. The first column stays put as you scroll sideways."},{"label":"Age buckets","value":"The same 0-30, 31-60, 61-90, and 91+ day buckets as AP Aging. Each column sorts and shows currency."},{"label":"Totals row","value":"The bottom row sums each bucket and shows the grand Open total."},{"label":"Status label","value":"'Ties to control' (green) when the report agrees with your accounts-receivable control account, or 'Out of Balance' (red)."}]},{"heading":"Balance Sheet","items":[{"label":"Purpose","value":"A snapshot of your financial position on a date: Assets, Liabilities, and Equity."},{"label":"Sections","value":"Assets, Liabilities, and Equity. Each line shows account number, name, and amount, with a section subtotal."},{"label":"Current Year Earnings","value":"A dedicated equity line. Total Equity is shown with this year's earnings folded in."},{"label":"Footer","value":"Total Liabilities and Equity, which ties to Total Assets when the sheet is balanced."},{"label":"Status label","value":"'Balanced' (green) when assets equal liabilities plus equity, or 'Out of Balance' (red)."}]},{"heading":"Bank Reconciliation","items":[{"label":"Purpose","value":"Matches your cash balance to a bank statement by checking off which entries have cleared the bank."},{"label":"Start form","value":"Pick a Cash Account, enter a Statement Date and an Ending Balance, then click Start to open a worksheet."},{"label":"Summary","value":"Shows your Book Balance, the Statement Ending Balance, the Cleared total, and the Outstanding total."},{"label":"Cleared checkbox","value":"Each row has a checkbox to mark an entry cleared. Checking it only stages the change. Nothing is saved until you click 'Update cleared', and a count of unsaved changes shows next to the button."},{"label":"Difference","value":"The header shows 'Reconciled' (green) when the difference is zero, otherwise it shows the Difference amount (amber)."},{"label":"Status and Finalize","value":"A worksheet is Draft or Finalized. You can finalize only when it's reconciled and there are no unsaved cleared changes. When no worksheet is open, a list of past reconciliations shows; click a row to reopen it."}]},{"heading":"Cash Flow","items":[{"label":"Purpose","value":"Shows how cash moved across operating, investing, and financing activity."},{"label":"Operating","value":"Starts from Net Income, applies operating adjustments, and subtotals Net Cash From Operating."},{"label":"Investing","value":"Shown only when there's investing activity; subtotals Net Cash From Investing."},{"label":"Financing","value":"Lists financing activity and subtotals Net Cash From Financing. Shows a placeholder when there's none."},{"label":"Footer","value":"Net Change In Cash, then a row that checks it against the actual cash movement."},{"label":"Status label","value":"'Reconciled' (green) when the net change matches the actual cash movement, or 'Out of Balance' (red)."}]},{"heading":"GRNI — Goods Received Not Invoiced","items":[{"label":"Purpose","value":"Checks the receiving clearing account: goods you've physically received but the vendor hasn't billed yet."},{"label":"Summary","value":"Shows what your books hold in the clearing account, the open amount your operations report, and the Variance between them."},{"label":"Open by Purchase Order","value":"Breaks the open amount down by purchase order across the age buckets, with an Open Amount per row. A totals row sums each bucket and the grand Open total."},{"label":"Uncovered receipts","value":"When present, lists received items that don't tie to an open purchase order. The heading shows a count."},{"label":"Status label","value":"'Reconciled' (green) when the clearing account equals the open amount, otherwise 'Variance'."}]},{"heading":"Period Close","items":[{"label":"Purpose","value":"Manages your fiscal years and their periods, controlling what can still be posted."},{"label":"Fiscal year","value":"Each year shows a name and an Open or Closed label. An open year has a 'Close Year' action."},{"label":"Periods","value":"Each year lists its periods with a date range and a status label."},{"label":"Period statuses","value":"Open (green) allows posting. Soft Closed (amber) blocks routine posting but can be reopened. Hard Closed (muted) is locked for good."},{"label":"Period actions","value":"From Open: Soft Close or Hard Close. From Soft Closed: Reopen or Hard Close. Hard Closed shows 'Locked' with no further actions. Buttons disable while a close or reopen is running."}]},{"heading":"Profit & Loss","items":[{"label":"Purpose","value":"The income statement for the period: revenue, expenses, and the resulting net income."},{"label":"Income lines","value":"Each income line shows account number, name, and amount, subtotaled as Total Income (a placeholder shows when there's none)."},{"label":"Expense lines","value":"Each expense line shows account number, name, and amount, subtotaled as Total Expense (a placeholder shows when there's none)."},{"label":"Net Income","value":"The footer figure: Total Income minus Total Expense."},{"label":"Margin note","value":"When cost of goods sold hasn't posted, a note at the top warns that the margin is incomplete. It goes away once cost of goods sold posts."}]},{"heading":"Trial Balance","items":[{"label":"Purpose","value":"Lists every account with its debit total, credit total, and net balance. It's the foundation report for all the statements."},{"label":"Columns","value":"Account Number, Account, Debit, Credit, and Net. Debit, Credit, and Net sort and show currency, right-aligned."},{"label":"Totals row","value":"The bottom row shows Total Debit and Total Credit, which are equal when the books balance."},{"label":"Status label","value":"'Balanced' (green) when total debits equal total credits, or 'Out of Balance' (red). If the trial balance is out of balance, you can't trust the other statements."}]},{"heading":"Shared Patterns","items":[{"label":"Auto-refresh","value":"Most reports refresh on their own when your accounting activity changes, so there's no need to reload by hand."},{"label":"Statement vs table","value":"Profit & Loss, Balance Sheet, Cash Flow, and the GRNI summary read like financial statements. Trial Balance, AR and AP Aging, the GRNI purchase-order breakdown, Period Close, and Bank Statements read like tables you can sort and filter."},{"label":"Single set of books","value":"Reports run against a single set of books today. Support for multiple sets of books is planned."},{"label":"Home tiles","value":"The Accounting home page is a grid of tiles that open each report plus the supporting tools (Bank Statements import and Exports)."}]}]}"""
