            ContentJson = """{"appRoute":"/accounting/exports","startButtonLabel":"Tour the Exports Page","steps":[{"element":"app-page-header","popover":{"title":"The Exports Page","description":"This page hands your books to an outside accountant without giving them a login. It has two halves: CSV downloads that are always available, and — only when your install turns it on — a one-way send to QuickBooks Online. Reach it from the Exports tile on the Accounting home page.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":".exports-toolbar","popover":{"title":"Pick the Date Range First","description":"Every export uses this date range. It defaults to month-to-date and offers two shortcuts, This Month and Last 30 Days, or set your own start and end. Choose the period you're delivering before you download or send.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":".exports-buttons","popover":{"title":"The Three CSV Downloads","description":"Each button downloads a file your accountant can open in Excel. Trial Balance CSV is the account-level snapshot they reconcile against. GL Detail CSV is the line-by-line entries behind it. Journal Summary CSV is the period rolled up to one net per account. Only one download runs at a time.","side":"top"}},{"element":".exports-section","popover":{"title":"CSV Is Always Available","description":"The CSV section needs no setup and no connection. It's the universal way to share with any accountant. Below it, a QuickBooks section appears only when your install has turned on the QuickBooks send and connected QuickBooks. If you don't see that section, CSV is your path.","side":"top"}},{"element":".page-content","popover":{"title":"One-Way, Never a Sync","description":"When the QuickBooks send is on, it posts the period's per-account net as one balanced journal entry into QuickBooks Online — a copy going out, never read back. A send is refused if an account with activity isn't matched to a QuickBooks account, or if the range overlaps a period you already sent. Forge always keeps the books; the export is a copy going out.","side":"top"}}]}"""
