t) or Ignore the line (park it). Confirmed lines turn green; Unmatch reverses a decision and sends the line back to the queue."},{"id":"ax7","text":"What is the relationship between the Bank Statements page and the Bank Reconciliation worksheet?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"They are unrelated — Bank Statements is just an archive of uploaded files"},{"id":"b","text":"The matches you confirm on Bank Statements are the lines that show as cleared on the Bank Reconciliation worksheet","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Bank Reconciliation imports the file; Bank Statements finalizes it"},{"id":"d","text":"Confirming a match automatically finalizes the reconciliation"}],"explanation":"Confirming a match is your way of saying the bank settled that entry, which is exactly what Bank Reconciliation needs. So you import and confirm matches on the Bank Statements page, then open Bank Reconciliation, where the cleared total reflects your confirmations and you finalize once you tie out."}]}"""
